WEBVTT


00:00:18.563 --> 00:00:21.896
It's the first time I've seen you
decline a request, Attorney Kujo.

00:00:22.563 --> 00:00:25.230
Why did you turn down
Hanae Iemori's request?

00:00:25.813 --> 00:00:29.480
Because it'd be troublesome to be accused
of a conflict of interest later on.

00:00:29.980 --> 00:00:33.813
Is that because you used to work
at Attorney Yamashiro's firm?

00:00:33.896 --> 00:00:37.230
I worked there for about five years
before I became independent.

00:00:38.146 --> 00:00:40.855
Has he always had a bad reputation?

00:00:40.938 --> 00:00:41.938
No.

00:00:42.688 --> 00:00:46.355
He used to be well-liked
and respected by others in the profession.

00:00:46.438 --> 00:00:47.688
It was only…

00:00:48.188 --> 00:00:50.896
He made a name for himself
by handling a big case.

00:00:51.396 --> 00:00:54.188
Then he began expanding
into side businesses.

00:00:55.230 --> 00:00:56.605
That got him into debt.

00:00:56.688 --> 00:01:00.021
And he had an anti-social force
cover his debt?

00:01:00.105 --> 00:01:05.063
As a result, he's now in a position
where he's forced to help them.

00:01:06.230 --> 00:01:08.355
Money is scary.

00:01:08.980 --> 00:01:11.105
It is scary.

00:01:57.938 --> 00:02:00.105
Hello, Attorney Nagaragi.

00:02:00.646 --> 00:02:02.646
It's been a while, Attorney Kurama.

00:02:03.146 --> 00:02:05.396
I now go by the name Kujo.

00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:08.730
Oh, that's right.
It's your wife's last name.

00:02:09.230 --> 00:02:10.605
My ex-wife.

00:02:11.188 --> 00:02:13.605
My apologies. Is work going well?

00:02:14.188 --> 00:02:17.146
Thanks to your teachings,
I've been able to get by.

00:02:17.230 --> 00:02:19.021
So what did you wanna talk about?

00:02:19.688 --> 00:02:23.480
I'm debating whether
to go up against an attorney I know.

00:02:24.605 --> 00:02:27.813
Since you're debating it,
is it someone quite close to you?

00:02:31.980 --> 00:02:35.105
Then listen to me
as if I'm just talking to myself.

00:02:35.938 --> 00:02:37.730
-Let's walk a little.
-Sure.

00:02:39.396 --> 00:02:41.730
"The law is nothing
but the ethical minimum."

00:02:41.813 --> 00:02:44.813
Those are the words
of the German jurist Jellinek.

00:02:45.355 --> 00:02:49.188
Even if something is ethically wrong,
it may not violate the law.

00:02:50.105 --> 00:02:52.855
Ordinary people may flaunt
their ethics on social media,

00:02:52.938 --> 00:02:54.688
but the law is a different matter.

00:02:55.188 --> 00:02:57.813
Everyone sees ethics differently anyway.

00:02:58.938 --> 00:03:02.480
The law can be cold
and heartless at times.

00:03:02.980 --> 00:03:06.396
If you abuse it,
it can become extremely unethical.

00:03:07.438 --> 00:03:09.313
So it shouldn't be mistaken,

00:03:10.646 --> 00:03:13.855
but an attorney works
for the benefit of their client.

00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:16.855
A client who has
little knowledge of the law

00:03:16.938 --> 00:03:19.355
places their full trust in their attorney.

00:03:20.271 --> 00:03:23.605
Because of that,
they follow everything the attorney says,

00:03:23.688 --> 00:03:27.605
and end up paying an outrageous amount
of money and signing an unjust document.

00:03:27.688 --> 00:03:30.688
Attorneys who greedily pursue money
for their own selfish gain,

00:03:30.771 --> 00:03:34.980
instead of serving their clients'
best interests, are a disgrace.

00:03:35.771 --> 00:03:36.730
Yes.

00:03:39.563 --> 00:03:41.188
So Attorney Kujo,

00:03:41.980 --> 00:03:44.646
only the son can stop
the parents' madness.

00:03:47.438 --> 00:03:49.646
Put a stop
to Attorney Yamashiro's madness.

00:03:54.771 --> 00:03:56.688
Attorney Kujo,

00:03:56.771 --> 00:03:58.688
shall we order room service?

00:03:59.313 --> 00:04:01.230
I'm really fine.

00:04:02.146 --> 00:04:07.855
But you gave all your assets
to your ex-wife and live in a tent, right?

00:04:07.938 --> 00:04:09.438
At least eat properly.

00:04:10.021 --> 00:04:12.688
I've recently changed
to eating one meal a day.

00:04:13.188 --> 00:04:15.355
My focus is improved through hunger,

00:04:15.438 --> 00:04:17.813
and I rest my stomach
for more than 16 hours.

00:04:17.896 --> 00:04:22.021
-The autophagy effect boosts my immunity.
-What the heck is that?

00:04:22.105 --> 00:04:23.521
Whatever. Just eat.

00:04:23.605 --> 00:04:27.730
What parent wouldn't worry
about their son's health?

00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:33.146
Oh, hi. It's Mr. Yamashiro. Well…

00:04:33.646 --> 00:04:34.896
Meat and bread. Yeah.

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:37.646
And beer. Right away.

00:04:37.730 --> 00:04:38.980
I said, beer!

00:04:39.063 --> 00:04:41.646
I said to hurry. Yeah, okay.

00:04:43.438 --> 00:04:44.813
Meat in the morning?

00:04:45.521 --> 00:04:47.313
If you're in the prime of life,

00:04:47.396 --> 00:04:50.480
you should eat meat in the morning
and get energized.

00:04:51.771 --> 00:04:54.938
Huh? So what did you want to talk about?

00:04:58.230 --> 00:05:01.480
As the legal representative
of Shigenori Iemori's heir,

00:05:01.563 --> 00:05:03.188
and under my duties as executor,

00:05:04.521 --> 00:05:08.063
I request that you disclose
the inventory of assets and the will.

00:05:13.605 --> 00:05:17.105
He's the one who, in his will,
left the entire amount to Kikogi,

00:05:17.605 --> 00:05:19.480
which runs the nursing home.

00:05:21.355 --> 00:05:23.271
I contacted the financial institution.

00:05:23.355 --> 00:05:26.313
And I discovered that you,
the executor of the will,

00:05:26.396 --> 00:05:28.813
withdrew the entire amount.

00:05:28.896 --> 00:05:32.938
I simply executed the will
in accordance with the law.

00:05:33.938 --> 00:05:37.230
But Mr. Iemori, who passed away,
had advanced dementia.

00:05:37.313 --> 00:05:38.980
He was unable to communicate.

00:05:40.646 --> 00:05:44.271
We may file a criminal suit for forgery
of private documents and seals,

00:05:44.355 --> 00:05:47.396
use of forged documents, or compulsion.

00:05:47.480 --> 00:05:49.230
If you want to see the will,

00:05:49.313 --> 00:05:50.563
here you go.

00:05:53.605 --> 00:05:55.688
The person clearly wrote this himself.

00:05:57.355 --> 00:06:00.230
I, SHIGENORI IEMORI,
DO HEREBY DECLARE THIS TO BE MY WILL.

00:06:00.313 --> 00:06:02.646
APPOINTED EXECUTOR OF MY WILL -
YUZO YAMASHIRO

00:06:02.730 --> 00:06:04.230
TESTATOR - SHIGENORI IEMORI

00:06:07.230 --> 00:06:10.855
Well, I don't mind fighting.

00:06:10.938 --> 00:06:14.896
But I care about you like my own son.

00:06:15.605 --> 00:06:17.396
If you are dissatisfied,

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:20.938
why don't we settle this
by my paying the reserved share amount?

00:06:22.063 --> 00:06:23.480
In that case,

00:06:23.563 --> 00:06:27.480
half of the assets, 200 million,
will go to the daughter.

00:06:28.146 --> 00:06:28.980
How's that?

00:06:30.188 --> 00:06:31.230
No.

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:36.063
My client is seeking
the return of all assets.

00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:38.855
I'm not considering anything else.

00:06:38.938 --> 00:06:41.938
Well, then, Attorney Kujo,

00:06:42.688 --> 00:06:46.896
are you willing to take me,
your own parent, down with you?

00:06:50.063 --> 00:06:51.896
-Yes.
-"Yes"?

00:06:52.521 --> 00:06:53.605
"Yes"?

00:06:56.896 --> 00:06:57.730
Yes.

00:06:57.813 --> 00:06:59.438
Did you really say, "Yes"?

00:07:00.021 --> 00:07:03.271
Who helped you become an attorney?

00:07:03.355 --> 00:07:04.355
Show some respect.

00:07:04.438 --> 00:07:05.938
As my parent taught me…

00:07:08.105 --> 00:07:10.396
I'm merely siding with my client.

00:07:12.938 --> 00:07:15.730
I don't understand your complex ramblings.

00:07:15.813 --> 00:07:17.855
So as I said…

00:07:17.938 --> 00:07:21.188
That aside, just make sure
to get back all the assets!

00:07:21.271 --> 00:07:23.021
Yes, yes.

00:07:23.105 --> 00:07:24.605
Only say "yes" once.

00:07:26.646 --> 00:07:29.063
I can't believe you took on
Ms. Iemori's request.

00:07:29.646 --> 00:07:31.480
There's no going back now.

00:07:31.563 --> 00:07:33.271
I know.

00:07:34.313 --> 00:07:37.730
So how do you plan to fight
against your mentor?

00:07:37.813 --> 00:07:40.105
I'm thinking it through right now.

00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:43.146
But you're at a complete disadvantage.

00:07:43.938 --> 00:07:48.063
There's even a will written
by the late Shigenori Iemori.

00:07:48.688 --> 00:07:52.730
But Shigenori Iemori had dementia.

00:07:52.813 --> 00:07:55.480
I'm not sure
that he wrote the will voluntarily.

00:07:55.980 --> 00:07:59.771
Well, his daughter, Hanae,
said he was forced to write it.

00:07:59.855 --> 00:08:03.146
If only we could prove that.

00:08:04.771 --> 00:08:08.230
That'll be very difficult.

00:08:09.146 --> 00:08:13.355
After all, our opponent is cunning and
has come through many battles unscathed.

00:08:13.438 --> 00:08:14.771
But this was surprising.

00:08:16.605 --> 00:08:17.480
Surprising?

00:08:17.563 --> 00:08:20.021
I thought for sure
that you'd turn the case down.

00:08:20.938 --> 00:08:22.438
Why did you take it on?

00:08:30.021 --> 00:08:31.230
Now, then,

00:08:31.771 --> 00:08:33.521
shall we go out?

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:12.230
KIKOGI GENERAL INCORPORATED ASSOCIATION
KIKO NURSING HOME

00:09:21.230 --> 00:09:23.063
Hello, there.

00:09:23.146 --> 00:09:25.063
You must be the lawyer.

00:09:25.146 --> 00:09:28.230
It'll be a while before the CEO,
Mr. Sugawara, arrives.

00:09:28.313 --> 00:09:30.438
Would you like me to show you inside?

00:09:31.355 --> 00:09:33.146
Yes, please.

00:09:33.230 --> 00:09:35.021
Okay. Right this way.

00:09:37.938 --> 00:09:39.980
This is the playroom.

00:09:40.063 --> 00:09:42.396
The residents gather here

00:09:42.896 --> 00:09:44.355
and have fun like this.

00:09:49.146 --> 00:09:52.771
The facility is clean,
and the residents are cheerful.

00:09:52.855 --> 00:09:54.313
Thank you very much.

00:09:54.396 --> 00:09:55.938
Excuse me.

00:09:56.438 --> 00:09:57.438
Hello.

00:09:57.521 --> 00:09:59.063
Hello.

00:10:00.563 --> 00:10:04.146
"A positive and bright future begins
with a believing heart."

00:10:04.230 --> 00:10:05.813
It's Mr. Sugawara's motto.

00:10:05.896 --> 00:10:10.313
Even if the person is elderly, if they
look ahead and believe in a bright future,

00:10:10.396 --> 00:10:12.230
they will gain hope for life.

00:10:12.730 --> 00:10:14.021
I see.

00:10:14.605 --> 00:10:16.355
They're coloring today.

00:10:39.563 --> 00:10:40.646
Hey.

00:10:41.605 --> 00:10:42.980
That area is off-limits.

00:10:43.063 --> 00:10:45.646
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:10:46.521 --> 00:10:47.688
Kuga.

00:10:52.313 --> 00:10:53.188
Oh,

00:10:53.771 --> 00:10:55.313
are you Attorney Kujo?

00:10:56.396 --> 00:10:57.271
Yes.

00:10:57.355 --> 00:10:59.813
Mr. Sugawara is too busy to meet with you.

00:11:00.980 --> 00:11:02.313
Can you go now?

00:11:02.396 --> 00:11:04.480
But we have an appointment.

00:11:05.355 --> 00:11:06.771
Please make another.

00:11:06.855 --> 00:11:08.105
Understood.

00:11:08.938 --> 00:11:10.938
Let's leave, Attorney Karasuma.

00:11:11.021 --> 00:11:13.980
-Huh? But we haven't seen anything yet.
-Let's leave.

00:11:30.271 --> 00:11:31.605
Are you sure?

00:11:33.271 --> 00:11:36.355
They weren't going to show us
the important area anyway.

00:11:36.438 --> 00:11:38.271
Well, that's probably true.

00:11:38.855 --> 00:11:39.938
Attorney Karasuma.

00:11:40.021 --> 00:11:40.855
Yes?

00:11:41.355 --> 00:11:44.313
I have a small favor to ask.

00:11:59.438 --> 00:12:06.021
"A positive and bright future begins
with a believing heart."

00:12:29.771 --> 00:12:32.230
Hey there!

00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:36.688
You can't do that, Mr. Udagawa.

00:12:36.771 --> 00:12:38.855
You can't go out without permission.

00:12:38.938 --> 00:12:41.105
You broke the rules,

00:12:41.188 --> 00:12:43.563
so let's stay quiet for a week.

00:12:44.855 --> 00:12:46.646
I'm hungry.

00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:50.730
Sure thing. Curry or ramen?

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:53.146
I don't want anything cold.

00:12:53.230 --> 00:12:56.646
I want warm rice and miso soup.

00:12:56.730 --> 00:13:00.188
The curry and ramen here
are delicious when they're cold.

00:13:00.271 --> 00:13:01.980
Don't be too demanding.

00:13:02.980 --> 00:13:04.230
Hey.

00:13:04.313 --> 00:13:06.396
Do you want to get a hole in your stomach

00:13:06.480 --> 00:13:10.313
and have us feed you liquid food directly,
like Mr. Iwai in the next bed?

00:13:11.313 --> 00:13:12.313
No way.

00:13:12.396 --> 00:13:14.355
Then you have to endure it.

00:13:15.730 --> 00:13:17.563
"A positive and bright future begins

00:13:18.063 --> 00:13:20.521
with a believing heart."

00:13:20.605 --> 00:13:21.438
Go on.

00:13:22.521 --> 00:13:24.396
"A positive

00:13:24.896 --> 00:13:25.813
and bright…"

00:13:25.896 --> 00:13:27.438
Louder!

00:13:27.521 --> 00:13:30.438
"A positive and bright future…"

00:13:30.521 --> 00:13:32.105
Louder!

00:13:32.188 --> 00:13:36.605
"A positive and bright future begins
with a believing heart!"

00:13:36.688 --> 00:13:38.313
Okay. One more time.

00:13:38.396 --> 00:13:39.646
"A positive…"

00:13:59.313 --> 00:14:01.563
Mr. Udagawa's done with his meal.

00:14:01.646 --> 00:14:02.605
Got it.

00:14:03.188 --> 00:14:04.563
Did he eat everything?

00:14:05.146 --> 00:14:08.021
I forced the cold curry into his mouth.

00:14:08.521 --> 00:14:11.313
I tried it once.
It was the most disgusting thing.

00:14:13.105 --> 00:14:14.355
Hey, have you

00:14:15.646 --> 00:14:16.646
got used to the job?

00:14:17.896 --> 00:14:18.813
Yeah.

00:14:19.521 --> 00:14:22.855
This place is chill with the staff.
It's freaking awesome.

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.605
Mr. Sugawara

00:14:26.688 --> 00:14:29.688
sees caregiving simply as a business.

00:14:29.771 --> 00:14:32.063
If the residents are kept in the facility,

00:14:32.146 --> 00:14:35.188
the cost of traveling to their homes
will be reduced.

00:14:35.688 --> 00:14:39.146
And the payments will keep coming in
until the residents die.

00:14:39.646 --> 00:14:41.730
He said it's like a subscription.

00:14:41.813 --> 00:14:43.438
Subscription?

00:14:43.938 --> 00:14:45.146
So true.

00:14:45.646 --> 00:14:47.938
The elderly people let their money rot.

00:14:48.021 --> 00:14:52.980
He said we can bury them in care services
and use up the system's full limit.

00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:58.271
He squeezed a lot of money
out of Mr. Iemori, who just died.

00:15:00.021 --> 00:15:01.646
Mr. Iemori, huh?

00:15:03.021 --> 00:15:04.605
He was a lot of work.

00:15:04.688 --> 00:15:06.480
He was rebellious,

00:15:06.563 --> 00:15:08.688
so I punched him and broke his rib.

00:15:10.188 --> 00:15:12.896
By the way, my supervisor had me

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:16.438
make Mr. Iemori practice writing
the same sentences every day.

00:15:16.521 --> 00:15:19.313
He was rebellious sometimes
and didn't want to write.

00:15:19.396 --> 00:15:22.063
So every time that happened,
I flicked his broken rib.

00:15:24.396 --> 00:15:27.271
His facial expression was so funny
that I had to film it.

00:15:27.355 --> 00:15:28.480
Do you want to see?

00:15:28.980 --> 00:15:29.813
Yeah.

00:15:29.896 --> 00:15:33.688
Executor! Executor of will!

00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:39.313
Got it? Hurry up and do it.

00:15:39.396 --> 00:15:40.896
Don't stop, don't stop. Don't.

00:15:40.980 --> 00:15:42.938
I… I can't breathe.

00:15:50.521 --> 00:15:53.230
Don't you dare leave evidence of abuse.

00:15:53.313 --> 00:15:54.313
Mr. Sugawara.

00:15:54.396 --> 00:15:55.230
Huh?

00:15:58.938 --> 00:16:02.313
Do you save your photos
and the like to the cloud?

00:16:02.813 --> 00:16:04.105
No.

00:16:13.188 --> 00:16:16.688
Smartphones, these days, don't break
when they're submerged in water.

00:16:34.855 --> 00:16:36.896
When you climb to the top,

00:16:37.396 --> 00:16:40.563
drop your phone, and destroy it.

00:16:42.438 --> 00:16:44.230
Y-Yes!

00:16:46.980 --> 00:16:49.480
Mr. Sugawara, I'll throw your coffee away.

00:16:52.563 --> 00:16:55.355
I didn't wash my hands
after using the bathroom earlier.

00:16:55.896 --> 00:16:57.855
Bacteria are growing in there.

00:16:58.355 --> 00:16:59.521
That's dirty.

00:16:59.605 --> 00:17:00.438
Drink it.

00:17:02.063 --> 00:17:02.896
Huh?

00:17:10.521 --> 00:17:11.355
Drink it.

00:17:14.521 --> 00:17:15.396
Yes.

00:17:28.438 --> 00:17:32.021
I look at the dying,
old people in our facility,

00:17:32.521 --> 00:17:35.730
and I always think
they're a lot like this country.

00:17:36.563 --> 00:17:39.313
By "this country," do you mean Japan?

00:17:40.396 --> 00:17:42.313
With the elderly population growing,

00:17:42.396 --> 00:17:45.146
Japan's tax revenue
will rely on the working population,

00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:46.605
which is half of the total.

00:17:47.105 --> 00:17:50.521
The wealthy know how
to avoid paying taxes.

00:17:50.605 --> 00:17:54.730
The burden will fall on salaried workers,
with taxes squeezed from their paychecks.

00:17:54.813 --> 00:17:56.563
I made it to the top!

00:18:00.438 --> 00:18:01.646
Drop it.

00:18:02.813 --> 00:18:04.021
Yes!

00:18:04.855 --> 00:18:06.938
Hey, your voice is too small.

00:18:08.896 --> 00:18:10.271
Yes!

00:18:27.105 --> 00:18:28.521
Kuga,

00:18:29.105 --> 00:18:30.563
give me the coffee.

00:18:35.605 --> 00:18:38.855
We only take the good stuff.

00:18:38.938 --> 00:18:41.563
And we'll abandon the country
that's about to die,

00:18:42.230 --> 00:18:45.188
move to a country that's on the rise,

00:18:45.688 --> 00:18:47.771
and live a life of ease.

00:19:06.146 --> 00:19:08.313
We're brothers who shared a cup.

00:19:11.188 --> 00:19:13.063
I'll kill you if you betray me.

00:19:16.855 --> 00:19:17.980
Yes.

00:19:21.021 --> 00:19:22.896
CHINESE CUISINE
BEIJING RESTAURANT

00:19:22.980 --> 00:19:24.396
Thank you very much.

00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:25.938
Welcome! Come on in. Please.

00:19:26.021 --> 00:19:27.771
Eat as much as you want.

00:19:27.855 --> 00:19:30.980
Please take me to a counter-only
sushi restaurant occasionally,

00:19:31.063 --> 00:19:34.063
or a teppanyaki place
where the chef cooks in front of you.

00:19:34.146 --> 00:19:36.271
We always end up going
to places like this.

00:19:36.771 --> 00:19:38.230
Hey!

00:19:38.313 --> 00:19:41.730
Ms. Yakushimae,
"Places like this"? Isn't that rude?

00:19:41.813 --> 00:19:45.646
But look at this place!
All the autographs are fake.

00:19:45.730 --> 00:19:47.730
They're real.

00:19:50.021 --> 00:19:52.855
Morgan Freeman would never come here.

00:19:54.146 --> 00:19:56.355
Hey, Attorney Karasuma,
this is fraud, right?

00:19:56.438 --> 00:19:59.355
-Huh?
-Maybe I should sue this restaurant.

00:19:59.438 --> 00:20:03.646
When our current case settles down,
let's have Attorney Kujo take us out.

00:20:05.021 --> 00:20:06.480
You promised.

00:20:07.688 --> 00:20:09.813
Did you find out anything
about Ms. Iemori?

00:20:09.896 --> 00:20:10.730
Oh…

00:20:13.063 --> 00:20:16.980
Did you know Ms. Iemori's father
used to run a famous jewelry store?

00:20:17.813 --> 00:20:22.730
I knew he ran a jewelry store,
but I didn't know it was famous.

00:20:22.813 --> 00:20:25.396
It wasn't that it was making
a lot of money.

00:20:25.480 --> 00:20:29.188
It was famous for not going bankrupt
despite not having any customers.

00:20:29.271 --> 00:20:31.480
There are stores like that sometimes.

00:20:31.563 --> 00:20:34.855
But the family owned land,
so they had plenty of money.

00:20:35.438 --> 00:20:38.605
And she had some disputes
with her younger brother and his wife.

00:20:38.688 --> 00:20:39.521
IEMORI

00:20:40.938 --> 00:20:44.188
Her younger brother, Keisuke,
works as an accountant.

00:20:44.271 --> 00:20:47.313
Hey, you're being inconsiderate
of the neighbors.

00:20:47.396 --> 00:20:49.813
His wife's name is Saeko.

00:20:49.896 --> 00:20:52.480
Before Shigenori developed dementia,

00:20:52.563 --> 00:20:55.855
it seems that she left
with Keisuke and his mother.

00:20:56.355 --> 00:20:59.646
So after that, Hanae cared for him alone?

00:20:59.730 --> 00:21:00.771
That's right.

00:21:01.438 --> 00:21:05.438
It was tough, with him wandering around
and running amok in the house.

00:21:06.271 --> 00:21:08.605
I consulted a friend of mine
who's a caregiver,

00:21:09.105 --> 00:21:12.605
and it seems like Shigenori had
a pretty severe case of dementia.

00:21:12.688 --> 00:21:14.063
How severe?

00:21:14.730 --> 00:21:16.188
Dementia

00:21:16.271 --> 00:21:22.230
can be divided into the four stages
of preclinical, early, middle, and late.

00:21:22.313 --> 00:21:25.521
Shigenori's cognitive abilities
had declined,

00:21:25.605 --> 00:21:27.938
and he was unable to recognize people

00:21:28.021 --> 00:21:31.188
and understand words,
which indicates the late stage.

00:21:32.563 --> 00:21:33.771
Late stage…

00:21:35.730 --> 00:21:37.230
Your total is 1,012 yen.

00:21:37.313 --> 00:21:38.313
Huh?

00:21:38.396 --> 00:21:39.813
It's 1,012 yen.

00:21:39.896 --> 00:21:41.855
Got it. Just a moment.

00:21:41.938 --> 00:21:42.813
Okay.

00:21:42.896 --> 00:21:45.730
I'm busy here.
What a slow and annoying old hag.

00:21:45.813 --> 00:21:46.730
Huh?

00:21:46.813 --> 00:21:49.021
Get your wallet out before you check out.

00:21:49.105 --> 00:21:50.105
I thought I had it.

00:21:50.188 --> 00:21:51.771
-Well, then…
-Yes.

00:21:51.855 --> 00:21:54.355
I'd like to use this.

00:21:54.438 --> 00:21:56.938
I'm sorry.
We don't accept electronic money.

00:21:57.021 --> 00:22:00.021
So many old people.

00:22:05.980 --> 00:22:08.480
OINTMENT

00:22:08.980 --> 00:22:10.480
This tastes bad.

00:22:10.563 --> 00:22:12.230
I'm sorry for the inconvenience.

00:22:14.438 --> 00:22:17.021
Excuse me. Please excuse me.

00:22:20.021 --> 00:22:20.855
Dad.

00:22:20.938 --> 00:22:22.563
Oh, no, no. No, no.

00:22:22.646 --> 00:22:25.563
Dad, let's go home.
Let's go home. Let's go home.

00:22:25.646 --> 00:22:27.063
I'm sorry.

00:22:27.146 --> 00:22:29.271
Ma'am, I need you to pay for that.

00:22:29.355 --> 00:22:31.146
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Dad!

00:22:31.230 --> 00:22:32.230
Don't be fooled.

00:22:32.313 --> 00:22:33.688
Stop, stop.

00:22:33.771 --> 00:22:35.730
-Don't be fooled.
-Dad, stop it.

00:22:35.813 --> 00:22:38.438
Dad, no, no.

00:22:39.896 --> 00:22:40.730
Dad?

00:22:41.938 --> 00:22:43.605
Hey, do you smell something?

00:22:44.896 --> 00:22:47.355
It really stinks. What could it be?

00:22:47.438 --> 00:22:48.313
Something stinks.

00:22:48.396 --> 00:22:49.271
It stinks.

00:22:49.355 --> 00:22:50.396
What is it?

00:22:51.313 --> 00:22:52.271
No way.

00:22:52.980 --> 00:22:55.188
Wait a minute… Hey, hey.

00:23:15.521 --> 00:23:17.396
There's a register open up front.

00:23:22.855 --> 00:23:24.563
Good morning, Attorney Kujo…

00:23:25.188 --> 00:23:27.188
Good morning, Attorney Karasuma.

00:23:32.188 --> 00:23:33.355
What happened?

00:23:33.980 --> 00:23:36.063
The office is a mess.

00:23:36.896 --> 00:23:39.188
Don't tell me there was a police raid.

00:23:42.938 --> 00:23:44.563
It was Black Thunder.

00:23:46.480 --> 00:23:50.938
When it doesn't get enough exercise,
this is what happens from stress.

00:23:51.980 --> 00:23:56.188
If we don't find a new owner soon,
we'll be forced to shut down our practice.

00:23:56.771 --> 00:23:58.688
So how did it go?

00:23:58.771 --> 00:24:00.563
The background check on Ms. Iemori.

00:24:01.063 --> 00:24:04.271
It seems like Shigenori's dementia
was quite severe.

00:24:04.855 --> 00:24:07.896
I don't think he was
in any condition to write a will.

00:24:08.396 --> 00:24:09.605
I see.

00:24:10.938 --> 00:24:16.480
Someone might have copied Shigenori's
handwriting and forged the will.

00:24:19.480 --> 00:24:21.480
Well, you see…

00:24:29.688 --> 00:24:30.771
This…

00:24:30.855 --> 00:24:32.980
It's Shigenori Iemori.

00:24:37.146 --> 00:24:39.188
He's writing the will himself.

00:24:41.146 --> 00:24:43.980
I sent this to the attorney
on the opposing side.

00:24:44.063 --> 00:24:45.688
Is that so?

00:24:49.271 --> 00:24:53.021
Anyway, this 3,000-yen hamburger
is delicious.

00:24:53.105 --> 00:24:54.188
Right?

00:24:54.688 --> 00:24:56.896
Apparently, it's a specialty
of this hotel.

00:24:57.521 --> 00:24:58.605
So,

00:24:59.855 --> 00:25:02.563
is everything okay, Attorney Yamashiro?

00:25:02.646 --> 00:25:04.230
Mr. Sugawara,

00:25:04.313 --> 00:25:05.896
don't worry.

00:25:06.563 --> 00:25:08.313
In a dispute,

00:25:08.396 --> 00:25:13.105
ideally, you want to get the other party
to submit without hurting them.

00:25:14.271 --> 00:25:15.938
Even if we fight in court,

00:25:16.021 --> 00:25:18.521
an obvious victory is meaningless.

00:25:19.105 --> 00:25:25.146
What's right is a settlement with
neither grand praise nor elegant honor.

00:25:27.605 --> 00:25:28.771
In other words,

00:25:28.855 --> 00:25:31.480
it's important to win without fighting.

00:25:33.480 --> 00:25:35.896
I showed him familial love.

00:25:37.938 --> 00:25:40.480
But Attorney Kujo bit back.

00:25:42.480 --> 00:25:45.021
He's already lost
before the fight has begun.

00:25:53.438 --> 00:25:54.980
Dad…

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:57.188
How could this happen?

00:25:57.271 --> 00:26:00.730
It was probably made
under Attorney Yamashiro's instructions.

00:26:01.480 --> 00:26:03.605
Since it's handwritten, the will is valid.

00:26:03.688 --> 00:26:06.396
He's trying to resolve this quickly
with a settlement.

00:26:06.896 --> 00:26:10.105
Settlement? You mean,
we must settle for 200 million? For half?

00:26:10.188 --> 00:26:12.355
No, I can't accept that.

00:26:12.438 --> 00:26:16.021
But Attorney Yamashiro is well-prepared.

00:26:16.688 --> 00:26:18.980
In addition to the video
of writing the will,

00:26:19.063 --> 00:26:22.313
the primary doctor is likely in league
with the nursing home.

00:26:22.396 --> 00:26:25.646
The doctor won't disclose
any medical records unfavorable to them.

00:26:26.230 --> 00:26:29.480
It's like a perfect crime
with no evidence.

00:26:29.563 --> 00:26:31.563
There's nothing we can do.

00:26:32.438 --> 00:26:34.813
In court, Attorney Yamashiro's
ironclad defense

00:26:34.896 --> 00:26:37.438
will give him a huge advantage.

00:26:38.938 --> 00:26:40.855
An ironclad defense, indeed.

00:26:42.563 --> 00:26:43.396
Ms. Iemori.

00:26:44.771 --> 00:26:47.813
Considering the cost-effectiveness
of a prolonged trial,

00:26:47.896 --> 00:26:51.980
it'd be wise to accept their offer
and take the statutory reserved share.

00:26:52.063 --> 00:26:52.980
No, no.

00:26:53.063 --> 00:26:55.438
Absolutely not. Absolutely not!

00:26:55.521 --> 00:26:59.438
Why do I have to give the inheritance
to some random nursing home?

00:26:59.521 --> 00:27:02.271
Isn't there a way to get
the entire amount back?

00:27:04.688 --> 00:27:06.355
If there is a way,

00:27:07.271 --> 00:27:08.938
it'd be by catching them unaware.

00:27:10.896 --> 00:27:12.021
Catching them unaware?

00:27:12.813 --> 00:27:16.396
Attorney Yamashiro
likely staged things meticulously

00:27:16.480 --> 00:27:19.730
because he saw the case
as legally problematic.

00:27:21.980 --> 00:27:22.813
So…

00:27:23.646 --> 00:27:26.313
It's important to win without fighting.

00:27:26.813 --> 00:27:28.730
My mentor taught me that.

00:27:30.563 --> 00:27:34.355
Attorney Yamashiro has already lost
before the fight has begun.

00:27:35.646 --> 00:27:38.688
Anyway, you have such a bad attitude.

00:27:39.188 --> 00:27:41.021
Put your feet down.

00:27:42.063 --> 00:27:42.896
Yes, yes.

00:27:43.396 --> 00:27:45.146
Only say "yes" once.

00:27:50.896 --> 00:27:54.896
Why is this happening? This is the worst.

00:27:55.563 --> 00:27:58.313
I heard some punks
are fighting with security.

00:27:58.396 --> 00:28:00.730
Hey, let us in. Hey!

00:28:01.313 --> 00:28:02.896
I'm calling the police!

00:28:03.605 --> 00:28:05.271
I said, let us in. Hey!

00:28:05.355 --> 00:28:06.230
Okay. Move aside.

00:28:06.313 --> 00:28:07.271
Huh?

00:28:31.521 --> 00:28:32.771
There we go.

00:28:36.480 --> 00:28:37.771
Mibu.

00:28:38.771 --> 00:28:40.313
You're late.

00:28:41.730 --> 00:28:43.146
Hey, you.

00:28:43.230 --> 00:28:45.105
What are you teaching your juniors?

00:28:46.980 --> 00:28:49.855
Did they come to wreck this place,
knowing I'm backing it?

00:28:51.521 --> 00:28:52.771
No.

00:28:53.480 --> 00:28:55.230
That's not it, Mr. Sugawara.

00:28:55.313 --> 00:28:58.646
You guys are interfering with business.

00:29:03.938 --> 00:29:05.605
How will you take responsibility?

00:29:06.605 --> 00:29:07.855
I'm sorry.

00:29:09.188 --> 00:29:10.021
Huh?

00:29:10.980 --> 00:29:12.563
I can't hear you.

00:29:13.521 --> 00:29:15.438
You lack sincerity.

00:29:16.813 --> 00:29:19.271
Get on your knees and apologize.

00:29:24.105 --> 00:29:25.271
Mibu.

00:29:27.396 --> 00:29:29.313
If you don't, I'll break his legs.

00:29:29.896 --> 00:29:30.855
Here.

00:29:36.188 --> 00:29:38.563
My junior was disrespectful.

00:29:41.021 --> 00:29:42.730
I'm sorry. Please forgive us.

00:29:42.813 --> 00:29:44.563
Mibu!

00:29:45.688 --> 00:29:47.105
You're pathetic.

00:29:48.730 --> 00:29:52.188
-Kuga, are you filming this?
-Yes, I am.

00:30:02.313 --> 00:30:04.730
Five million for the inconvenience.

00:30:06.021 --> 00:30:07.396
Bring it,

00:30:09.021 --> 00:30:10.313
Mibu.

00:30:16.521 --> 00:30:19.521
IEMORI

00:30:26.146 --> 00:30:28.980
Saeko, thank you for helping me.

00:30:29.480 --> 00:30:32.438
Let's allow the estate clean-out service
to handle the rest.

00:30:33.313 --> 00:30:34.563
Hanae,

00:30:34.646 --> 00:30:37.230
are these photo albums?

00:30:38.688 --> 00:30:39.521
Here.

00:30:43.813 --> 00:30:48.855
Hanae, you received 25 million as a gift
before your dad died. Where is it?

00:30:49.438 --> 00:30:52.771
I used it all up
on Dad's nursing care fees.

00:30:52.855 --> 00:30:53.771
What?

00:30:53.855 --> 00:30:56.105
You spent 25 million on nursing care fees?

00:30:56.188 --> 00:30:57.521
I can't believe it.

00:30:58.063 --> 00:30:59.646
It does cost that much.

00:30:59.730 --> 00:31:02.896
I know this best
because I took care of it all by myself.

00:31:02.980 --> 00:31:05.813
Oh, right, right.

00:31:05.896 --> 00:31:08.271
You took care of it all yourself,

00:31:08.355 --> 00:31:09.605
so that's why he ended up

00:31:09.688 --> 00:31:11.105
at a cheap nursing home.

00:31:11.188 --> 00:31:12.730
It wasn't cheap.

00:31:13.271 --> 00:31:14.396
Really?

00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:16.271
I read online that it was

00:31:16.355 --> 00:31:17.771
an "elderly dumping ground."

00:31:18.563 --> 00:31:20.188
And you used the money you saved

00:31:20.271 --> 00:31:22.355
to hire a massage therapist for yourself?

00:31:22.855 --> 00:31:24.521
I heard it from the neighbors.

00:31:24.605 --> 00:31:26.230
What's wrong with that?

00:31:26.313 --> 00:31:31.313
I was working, taking care of him,
and getting by on four hours of sleep.

00:31:33.271 --> 00:31:36.646
Well, I guess a housewife like you
wouldn't understand.

00:31:37.271 --> 00:31:38.396
Hey,

00:31:39.230 --> 00:31:41.480
are you looking down on housewives?

00:31:41.980 --> 00:31:43.646
The nursing home scammed you.

00:31:44.646 --> 00:31:47.438
If you believe that,
you guys should've cared for him.

00:31:47.521 --> 00:31:50.313
Why should I take care
of my father-in-law?

00:31:50.396 --> 00:31:53.438
I even helped your mother
go to the bathroom.

00:31:53.521 --> 00:31:56.313
How much money did I give you
for her living expenses?

00:31:56.396 --> 00:31:58.146
Enough already!

00:31:58.230 --> 00:32:01.271
I could've had a different life.

00:32:01.355 --> 00:32:04.521
My mother-in-law was always nagging me,
but I put up with it.

00:32:05.146 --> 00:32:06.230
Anyway,

00:32:06.313 --> 00:32:08.063
get back my stolen life

00:32:08.146 --> 00:32:10.563
and our share of the inheritance.

00:32:12.396 --> 00:32:15.355
Seriously… So hopeless.

00:32:27.855 --> 00:32:29.646
I'm exhausted.

00:32:43.521 --> 00:32:45.813
HANAE, SIX YEARS OLD
KEISUKE, FOUR YEARS OLD

00:32:45.896 --> 00:32:49.896
AUGUST 7TH
AT HACHIOJI CHILDREN'S AMUSEMENT PARK

00:32:56.230 --> 00:32:59.896
CHILDREN'S AMUSEMENT PARK TICKET
ADULT - 700 YEN

00:33:45.271 --> 00:33:46.813
Something smells good.

00:33:46.896 --> 00:33:48.355
Oh, Mibu.

00:33:48.980 --> 00:33:50.730
It's smoked meat.

00:33:50.813 --> 00:33:52.188
Would you like to join us?

00:33:52.271 --> 00:33:53.938
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

00:33:57.230 --> 00:33:58.396
Then I'll have some.

00:33:58.480 --> 00:33:59.355
Huh?

00:34:01.146 --> 00:34:03.313
You sure eat heartily!

00:34:10.605 --> 00:34:13.646
Beer on the roof
in the early evening is the best!

00:34:14.480 --> 00:34:16.063
It really is.

00:34:22.313 --> 00:34:23.521
Attorney Kujo.

00:34:27.605 --> 00:34:29.021
Here you go.

00:34:32.271 --> 00:34:34.730
Thank you. This will be very helpful.

00:34:35.855 --> 00:34:39.230
Well, I have some things to take care of,
so I'll be going now.

00:34:39.771 --> 00:34:41.188
Thank you for the food.

00:34:50.230 --> 00:34:51.980
Thank you.

00:35:16.563 --> 00:35:20.105
Attorney Kujo,
what was that USB drive for?

00:35:21.396 --> 00:35:25.188
It's our trump card to catch
Attorney Yamashiro unaware.

00:35:31.230 --> 00:35:33.146
Can I ask you again…?

00:35:34.521 --> 00:35:35.521
Go ahead.

00:35:36.021 --> 00:35:39.980
Why did you decide to go up against
your mentor Attorney Yamashiro?

00:35:43.480 --> 00:35:46.896
I'm simply prioritizing
my client's interests.

00:35:47.438 --> 00:35:52.355
It's just that Attorney Yamashiro's
and my client's opinions are at odds.

00:35:54.146 --> 00:35:56.146
Their opinions are at odds…

00:36:00.521 --> 00:36:05.230
So if our opinions were at odds,

00:36:05.855 --> 00:36:08.438
we'd go against each other, too, right?

00:36:18.813 --> 00:36:20.605
Don't say such scary things.

00:36:28.146 --> 00:36:29.646
Do you want some coffee?

00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:31.771
Yes, please.

00:36:42.813 --> 00:36:44.813
Hello, Attorney Yamashiro.

00:36:45.646 --> 00:36:47.313
Did you see the news?

00:36:47.396 --> 00:36:48.688
Yes.

00:36:52.521 --> 00:36:55.146
RAMPANT ABUSE AT CHIBA NURSING HOME

00:36:58.271 --> 00:37:00.271
Kujo, huh?

00:37:03.813 --> 00:37:05.771
What pollen are you reacting to now?

00:37:06.730 --> 00:37:09.480
At this time of year,
it's usually ragweed or rice,

00:37:10.646 --> 00:37:14.063
but I think someone is talking about me.

00:37:23.438 --> 00:37:26.480
RAMPANT ABUSE AT CHIBA NURSING HOME

00:37:26.563 --> 00:37:28.980
A FLICK TO A BROKEN RIB

00:37:29.063 --> 00:37:32.896
WAS USED AS A FORM OF "DISCIPLINE"

00:37:32.980 --> 00:37:35.730
RAMPANT ABUSE AT CHIBA NURSING HOME

00:37:42.271 --> 00:37:44.563
How many times are you going to fail?

00:37:44.646 --> 00:37:46.355
Got it? Hurry up and do it.

00:37:46.438 --> 00:37:48.396
Don't stop, don't stop. Don't.

00:37:49.063 --> 00:37:50.980
Hurry up and do it.

00:37:51.063 --> 00:37:52.771
PERSON A GROANS IN PAIN

00:40:41.063 --> 00:40:44.438
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa